## Quality & Testing

How we validate that skills actually work. Most skill repos ship without any quality assurance. We don't.

- **[Anthropic skill-creator](https://github.com/anthropics/skills/tree/main/skills/skill-creator)** — The eval framework we build on. Includes `run_eval.py` (binary assertion runner), `run_loop.py` (iterative improvement loop), `aggregate_benchmark.py` (variance analysis across runs), a Grader Agent, an Analyzer Agent, and an HTML benchmark viewer. Think of it as the Karpathy pattern applied to prompt engineering: write assertions, run them blind, iterate on the skill until they pass.

  **How Autopunk uses it:** Every skill in this repo goes through a two-stage quality gate. First, the AutoResearch loop — binary assertions that test whether a skill actually produces the output it promises (correct format, required elements present, no hallucinated structure). Skills iterate automatically until assertions pass. Second, our G-Eval scoring framework rates skills on usefulness, accuracy, and production-readiness. Skills that pass both stages get shipped. Skills that don't get rewritten or dropped. The assertion inputs and test cases live in `tests/` — you can run them yourself.
